  "texts": [
    "Secondly, LLMs are trained using publicly available data, which could include the HPO_GS, since it was initially published in 2015 and in turn could lead to a test data leakage.",
    "While this is indeed a realistic scenario, the expectations associated with it do not seem to be met by the poor results listed in Table 1 for Prompts 1-6 (we exclude Prompt 7 since it addresses directly in-context learning).",
    "Moreover, the same scenario does not hold for BIOC-GS (since it was not publicly available at the time of our experiments) and yet the results are significantly better.",
    "We argue that test data leakage is unlikely for scenarios similar to the ones presented in this paper because of the boost in efficiency provided by in-context learning.",
    "The F1 scores achieved on Prompt 7 are significantly better than all others, and hence we argue that the gap between results would have been smaller if the LLM would have just memorized the answers to the task (and hence the examples provided in Prompt 7 would not have helped as much)."
  ],
